<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<h2 id="head-3a570c11b3e08c97f2caba94112be74144c341a7">Demonshield of Gothmog [13,+13] (+4)</h2>
<em>This shield has been taken from the corpse of a demon, some demonic energy is still coursing through it, giving life to any that wield it. It is from a group of items that once belonged to Gothmog, the High Captain of the Balrogs.</em> <p>
It increases your dexterity by 4. It makes you invisible. It sustains your strength, dexterity and constitution. It provides immunity to paralysis. It provides resistance to life draining. It allows you to levitate. It produces a fiery sheath. It can re-curse itself. It cannot be harmed by acid, cold, lightning or fire. 
</p>
<p>
It contains three spells from the Demon school of magic (like all Demonshields): 
</p>

    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
Doom Shield - Raises a mirror of pain around you, doing very high damage to your foes that dare hit you, but greatly reduces your armor 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Demon Cloak - Raises a mirror that can reflect bolts and arrows for a time 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
Unholy Word - Kills a pet to heal you. There is a chance that the pet won't die but will turn against you it will decrease with higher level 
</p>
</li>
</ol>

